# Aikido code-scanning configuration — repo-root, non-admin, version-controlled.
# Docs: https://help.aikido.dev/code-scanning/scanning-practices/ignore-via-code-with-aikido-files
#
# Why this file exists (cute-dbt#372):
# Aikido's SAST scanner flags every askama `{{ ... | safe }}` interpolation in
# templates/ as "Rendering unescaped input -> XSS (high)". For cute-dbt these
# are false positives BY CONSTRUCTION — see ARCHITECTURE.md §5 (Asset embedding /
# zero-egress gate). `|safe` renders only:
#   (a) compile-time, SHA-256-pinned, `include_str!`-embedded vendored assets
#       (Sakura/jQuery/DataTables/Mermaid/Cytoscape/dagre + first-party JS),
#       provenance-indexed in assets/MANIFEST.toml; and
#   (b) the report / DAG payload JSON, which is pre-escaped by
#       `payload_json_for_html_script` (src/adapters/render.rs) and
#       `json_for_html_script` (src/adapters/explore.rs) — both turn every
#       tag-opening `<` into the JSON escape `<`, asserted by the
#       `json_escapes_tag_opening_lt` unit test. `JSON.parse` round-trips the
#       original characters; the browser's HTML script-data state machine never
#       sees a `</script>`/`<!--`/`<tag` opener.
# None is unescaped user input. The emitted report additionally makes ZERO
# outbound requests over file:// (the headless zero-egress gate), so an embedded
# payload cannot exfiltrate even if it were hostile.
#
# Path matching here is simple string-inclusion (no globs/regex): any file whose
# full path contains `templates/` is excluded from Aikido scanning. The templates
# directory is pure askama render markup over the above two `|safe` sources — it
# carries no secrets, no lockfiles, and no real SAST sink — so excluding it
# removes the recurring `|safe` false-positive noise without masking a real
# surface. Aikido remains advisory (never a required status check).

exclude:
  paths:
    - templates/
